<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="268" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,158,184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[371,667,158,185]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="davyana" variety="magdae">
<emphasis box="[371,524,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Aloe davyana</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[578,667,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">magdae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a more southerly distribution range than 
<taxonomicName authority="var. davyana" box="[1170,1444,158,185]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="davyana" variety="davyana">
<emphasis box="[1170,1295,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">A. davyana</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1349,1444,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">davyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It occurs from south of Johannesburg in the vicinity of Ennerdale, Walkerville, Sebokeng, and Vanderbijlpark in 
<collectingRegion box="[136,234,230,256]" country="South Africa" name="Gauteng" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Gauteng</collectingRegion>
, and southward to Parys and Heilbron in the 
<collectingRegion box="[732,847,230,257]" country="South Africa" name="Free State" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Free State</collectingRegion>
, on both sides of the north-south running N1 highway. 
<bibRefCitation author="Reynolds, G. W." box="[136,385,266,293]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" refId="ref3267" refString="Reynolds, G. W. (1950) The aloes of South Africa. The Aloes of South Africa Book Fund, Johannesburg, 534 pp." type="book" year="1950">Reynolds (1950: 235)</bibRefCitation>
was aware of 
<taxonomicName box="[557,835,266,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="davyana" variety="magdae">
<emphasis box="[557,686,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">A. davyana</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[746,835,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">magdae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and referred to it as: “Forms near Parys and towards Heilbron (southern limit [of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schonland" authorityYear="1905" box="[455,581,302,329]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davyana">
<emphasis box="[455,581,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">A. davyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
])”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="268" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,281,338,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Habitat</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[317,614,338,365]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="davyana" variety="magdae">
<emphasis box="[317,470,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Aloe davyana</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[525,614,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">magdae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in scattered colonies in grassveld dotted with clumps of shrubs and trees.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="268" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,410,436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Eponymy</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[340,651,410,437]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="davyana" variety="magdae">
<emphasis box="[340,498,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Aloe davyana</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[562,651,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">magdae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named for Magda Nel (born Makopane [Potgietersrus], 
<collectingRegion country="South Africa" name="Limpopo" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Limpopo province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[250,398,446,472]" name="South Africa" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<date box="[412,618,446,473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" value="1957-11-05">
<collectingDate box="[412,618,446,473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" value="1957-11-05">5 November 1957</collectingDate>
</date>
–) (
<figureCitation box="[669,740,446,473]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="6.[136,229,2054,2076]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1037,2030]" captionTargetId="figure-411@6.[151,1436,1037,2030]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 7. Magda Nel (5 November 1957–) after whom Aloe davyana var. magdae is named." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6331915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6331915/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). 
<collectorName box="[764,842,446,472]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Magda</collectorName>
holds a 
<collectorName box="[943,1147,446,472]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">National Diploma</collectorName>
for 
<collectorName box="[1199,1448,446,472]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Research Technicians</collectorName>
: 
<collectorName box="[136,265,482,508]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Agriculture</collectorName>
and 
<collectorName box="[323,405,483,509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Botany</collectorName>
, which she was awarded in 1979 by the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CC8781FFD8841DFF12F9E4FE5AFC89:8EBA604CFFDA841DFCFDFE6AFB56FE11" box="[871,1269,482,508]" country="South Africa" county="Subtropical Fruit Research Station" municipality="Roodeplaat Research Station" name="Tshwane University of Technology" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" stateProvince="Limpopo">Tshwane University of Technology</location>
[at the time the 
<collectorName box="[136,354,518,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Technikon Pretoria</collectorName>
]. 
<collectorName box="[369,431,518,544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Since</collectorName>
1991 she is employed as herbarium assistant in the 
<collectorName box="[996,1383,518,544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">H.G.W.J. Schweickerdt Herbarium</collectorName>
of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CC8781FFD8841DFF12F9E4FE5AFC89:8EBA604CFFDA841DFF12FDA3FEC8FDA9" box="[136,363,554,581]" country="South Africa" county="Subtropical Fruit Research Station" municipality="Roodeplaat Research Station" name="Department of Plant" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" stateProvince="Limpopo">Department of Plant</location>
and 
<collectorName box="[417,570,554,580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Soil Sciences</collectorName>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CC8781FFD8841DFF12F9E4FE5AFC89:8EBA604CFFDA841DFDDFFDA2FC9FFDA9" box="[581,828,554,580]" country="South Africa" county="Subtropical Fruit Research Station" municipality="Roodeplaat Research Station" name="University of Pretoria" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" stateProvince="Limpopo">University of Pretoria</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[839,985,554,580]" name="South Africa" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectorName box="[995,1037,555,581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Her</collectorName>
responsibilities include maintenance of the nearly 130,000 preserved plant specimens, capturing data from specimen labels, assisting mainstream plant science students, and handling many plant identification requests from students and the public. 
<collectorName box="[1245,1323,626,652]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Magda</collectorName>
previously held appointments at the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[428,759,662,688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Roodeplaat Research Station</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<collectorName box="[773,862,662,688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Pretoria</collectorName>
(1980), at the 
<collectorName box="[1036,1104,662,688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Citrus</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectingCounty pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Subtropical Fruit Research Station</collectingCounty>
(now under the 
<collectorName box="[398,742,698,725]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Agricultural Research Council</collectorName>
) (1981–1987), and, through the then 
<collectorName box="[1161,1379,698,725]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Transvaal Museum</collectorName>
, at the 
<collectorName box="[136,501,734,761]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Desert Ecological Research Unit</collectorName>
at 
<collectorName box="[534,635,734,760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Gobabeb</collectorName>
on the edge of the 
<collectorName box="[847,1003,734,761]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Namib Desert</collectorName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1038,1134,734,760]" name="Namibia" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Namibia</collectingCountry>
(1987–1990). 
<collectorName box="[1299,1341,734,760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">She</collectorName>
is also an accomplished graphic and digital artist. 
<collectorName box="[587,665,770,796]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Magda</collectorName>
has a longstanding interest in aloes after she was exposed to growing these plants at a young age by her father and her uncle, 
<collectorName box="[767,979,806,832]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Oom At Koeleman</collectorName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, G. F." box="[1040,1170,806,832]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" pagination="77 - 80" refId="ref3546" refString="Smith, G. F. (1996) Arthur Koeleman (1915 - 1994). Bothalia 26 (1): 77 - 80. https: // doi. org / 10.4102 / abc. v 26 i 1.693" type="journal article" year="1996">Smith 1996</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, G. F. &amp; Figueiredo, E." pageId="7" pageNumber="268" refId="ref3588" refString="Smith, G. F. &amp; Figueiredo, E. (2015) Garden aloes. Growing and breeding cultivars and hybrids. Jacana Media (Pty), Ltd, Auckland Park, Johannesburg, xiv, 193 pp." type="book" year="2015">Smith &amp; Figueiredo 2015</bibRefCitation>
: v [page unnumbered], 17).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
